            "answer_text": "Yes, but casual. You're not there to find a wife. You're there to fill your brain with the tools you need to not have to work the window at Wendy's. Serious college romances usually end in tragedy when you two go your separate ways to advance your education, or one of you gives up your dreams to follow the other. This leads to tremendous resentment later in life. College romances make for excellent chick Flicks, but not so much in real life. Keep it in your pants and focus on your studies. Your parents aren't struggling financially just so you can have a wild fling with a hot co-ed. ",
